This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a method for improving the performance of convolutional neural networks through tensor decomposition and fine-tuning. It is also likely to belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as convolutional neural networks are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Additionally, it may belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as these fields are closely related to machine learning and neural networks. Finally, it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the paper discusses a method for optimizing the structure of convolutional neural networks.
